00:16:21.450 --> 00:16:22.600
I could come back.

00:16:23.330 --> 00:16:25.330
What if you didn't want to come back?

00:16:25.760 --> 00:16:27.060
He could go abroad.

00:16:27.360 --> 00:16:29.430
What if he didn't want to go abroad?

00:16:29.720 --> 00:16:31.710
I really could come back.

00:16:31.850 --> 00:16:32.330
Then...

00:16:35.690 --> 00:16:36.050
No.

00:16:37.360 --> 00:16:39.050
If you didn't want to come back,

00:16:39.050 --> 00:16:40.330
and he didn't want to go abroad,

00:16:40.330 --> 00:16:41.330
what would you do?

00:16:44.450 --> 00:16:45.380
What would we do?

00:16:46.210 --> 00:16:47.240
What would they do?

00:16:47.240 --> 00:16:48.090
What would they do?

00:16:48.090 --> 00:16:49.210
Break up!

00:16:49.570 --> 00:16:50.970
That's the thing
about long-distance relationships.

00:16:50.970 --> 00:16:52.570
So people who love each other
can still break up.

00:16:52.570 --> 00:16:53.330
Get it?

00:16:54.360 --> 00:16:56.050
Long-distance relationships, huh?

00:16:56.050 --> 00:16:57.840
People all face
birth, aging, sickness, and death.

00:16:57.840 --> 00:17:00.490
Separation by life and death is also
a kind of long-distance relationship.

00:17:00.490 --> 00:17:02.570
If one day my beloved
will eventually leave the world,

00:17:02.570 --> 00:17:04.900
